    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The performance issue comes from having to traverse the tree many times to persist each single new status. If I comment this line out\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/43972fb1b0d0e0d44c4244541b7a1c0e958d68e1/packages/beacon-state-transition/src/altair/block/processAttestation.ts#L81\r\n\r\nthe cost of processing the entire block goes from 100ms -> 23.1ms.\r\n\r\nWe must apply all the changes in batch at the end of processAttestations(). Maybe with https://github.com/ChainSafe/persistent-merkle-tree/pull/53 ? Also do some pre-aggregate the statuses that will end-up in the same chunk or some bit manipulation magic.\r\n\r\n",
